com.dooapp.gaedo.prevalence.space
Interface StorageSpace<Key extends Serializable>

Type Parameters:
Key - used key type, allow simpler coercion over entered keys
All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
SimpleStorageSpace
public interface StorageSpace<Key extends Serializable>
extends Serializable

A storage space is the root storage element of a prevalence layer. All data resides in that storage space. To a certain extend, this storage space can be seen as a map of containers, those containers being maps, collections, or simple objects. Notice most of this interface (with the notable exception of Key parameterized type) has been borrowed from excellent space4j Space interface (see its javadoc at http://www.space4j.org/api/org/space4j/Space.html)
